# Code Navigation — jCodeMunch MCP (Always Active)

**Never read full files to find code. Use jcodemunch-mcp tools instead.**

A background daemon (`com.medinovai.jcodemunch`) keeps every repo under `~/Github/` pre-indexed at all times — 179+ repos, 279k+ symbols, updated within 15 minutes of any git commit.

## Session Start Protocol (every session)

1. Call `list_repos` — confirm this repo is indexed (it almost certainly is)
2. If missing: `index_folder: { "path": "<current working directory>" }` — one-time, takes ~5s
3. Use the repo's short display name for all subsequent calls (e.g. `"AtlasOS"`, `"zeroTouchMarketing"`)

## Always Use These Tools

| Instead of... | Use this |
|---|---|
| Read a file to find a function | `search_symbols: { "repo": "...", "query": "functionName" }` |
| Read a file to understand a class | `get_file_outline: { "repo": "...", "file_path": "src/foo.py" }` |
| Open a whole file | `get_symbol: { "repo": "...", "symbol_id": "path::Name#kind" }` |
| Grep for a string | `search_text: { "repo": "...", "query": "string" }` |
| Understand repo structure | `get_repo_outline: { "repo": "..." }` |
| Get function + its imports | `get_context_bundle: { "repo": "...", "symbol_id": "..." }` |

## Symbol ID Format

```
<file_path>::<qualified_name>#<kind>
```

Examples:
- `src/main.py::UserService.login#method`
- `openclaw/skills/_runner/index.js::SkillRunner.executeSkill#method`
- `mcp-servers/llm-proxy/index.js::routeRequest#function`

## Only Fall Back to File Reads When

- You are about to **edit** a specific file (need exact content + line numbers)
- The MCP server is unreachable
- The file type is not indexed (images, PDFs, config-only YAML)

## Cost Impact

Every `search_symbols` + `get_symbol` call instead of reading a file saves ~40,000 tokens.
All AI summaries route to local Ollama fleet (`qwen2.5-coder:32b`) — zero commercial cost.
